steps.description:
This table top is a 3'x3' square of 3/4" thick plywood. The legs are 1½" x 1½" square and about 37" long, with triangular braces cut from 1½" x 8"x 12" wooden pieces. The legs are splayed out slightly to give the table strength, and to allow the rotary pendulum to swing without hitting a leg. Screw and/or glue the braces to the legs first, and then cut their tops together at a slight angle with a table or circular saw. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0b/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/0b/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/aid631836-v4-728px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Adjust the leg lengths to give a table-top height of about 37". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3e/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/3e/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/aid631836-v4-728px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you want to be able to fit the table through doorways without taking off the legs, you might need slightly shorter legs and pendulums. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/17/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/aid631836-v4-728px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut about 1" off the top of the rotary pendulum dowel, so it is slightly lower than the other two. Then mount an 11"x11" square of thin 1/8" board to the top of this pendulum, using a small oak block glued to it for support, with a 3/4" hole for the dowel. Wrap some tape around the top of the dowel to get a tight fit, or just glue it on. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/92/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/92/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet1.jpg/aid631836-v4-728px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use two rubber bands, or some clips, to hold the paper in place on the platform. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2f/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/2f/Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/aid631836-v4-728px-Make-a-Three-Pendulum-Rotary-Harmonograph-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
